1. *Ratnik* je spreman da se bori za svoju zemlju. (The *warrior* is ready to fight for his country.)
2. U drevnim vremenima, *ratnici* su se borili za svoje kraljeve i države. (In ancient times, *warriors* fought for their kings and states.)
3. Mladić je sanjao da postane *ratnik* od malih nogu. (The young man dreamed of becoming a *warrior* from an early age.)
4. *Ratnici* su se sakupljali u šatorima pre bitke. (The *warriors* gathered in tents before the battle.)
5. On je *ratnik* po duši, spreman je za borbu bez obzira na sve. (He is a *warrior* at heart, ready to fight no matter what.)
6. *Ratniku* je pripala čast da nosi zastavu u bitci. (The honor of carrying the flag in battle was given to the *warrior*.)
7. *Ratnik* je izvukao mač i krenuo u napad. (The *warrior* drew his sword and charged.)
8. *Ratnici* su se vratili s pobjedničkog bojnog polja. (The *warriors* returned from the victorious battlefield.)
9. Njegova hrabrost i odanost su ga učinili omiljenim *ratnikom* među ljudima. (His bravery and loyalty made him a favorite *warrior* among the people.)
10. *Ratnik* je bio ranjen u borbi, ali nije odustao od borbe. (The *warrior* was wounded in battle but did not give up the fight.)